(42, 1, '2020-09-26 10:31:46', '2020-09-26 02:31:46', '<!-- wp:media-text {\"mediaId\":16,\"mediaType\":\"image\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-media-text alignwide is-stacked-on-mobile\"><figure class=\"wp-block-media-text__media\"><img src=\"https://dlcph.com/read/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/commitment.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-16 size-full\"/></figure><div class=\"wp-block-media-text__content\"><!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"jt\"} -->\n<p class=\"jt\">Let us \'\'Aim Higher\" and always strive to do more than what is expected. Do not make the mistake of doing only the minimum requirement to get your bonuses when you work your DLC business. We will be very disappointed if leaders practice this and teach their organization the same.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"jt\"} -->\n<p class=\"jt\">When we wrote our marketing plan, we purposely lowered the minimum requirement to make it easy for all distributors to achieve the goal. What we do not want is that the distributors become complacent. Doing an extra 30% to 50% more than the minimum requirement should be the goal you set for yourself and your downlines.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:media-text -->', 'Aim Higher', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'aim-higher', '', '', '2021-03-09 00:08:20', '2021-03-08 16:08:20', '', 23, 'https://dlcph.com/read/?page_id=42', 1, 'page', '', 0),
