onal sales from DLC-branded products.<br></li><li>Any distributor who can break off a 24% line that does at least 4000 PV total sales volume for the cycle and also maintains a non-manager group sales volume of at least 4000 PV for the same cycle of which 40 PV is personal sales from DLC-branded products.<br></li><li>Any distributor who can break off two (2) 24% lines that does at least 4000 PV total sales volume for the cycle and also maintains a non-manager group sales volume of at least 500 PV for the same cycle of which 40 PV is personal sales from DLC-branded products.<br></li><li>Any distributor who can break off three (3) or more 24% lines that does at least 4000 PV total sales volume for the cycle, shall enjoy the benefit of zero (0) PV group requirement for the same cycle with 40 PV as personal sales from DLC-branded products.<br></li><li>can qualify for Semi-Monthly profit sharing.</li></ul><br></li><li>To qualify for Overriding Bonuses from sponsored groups, the 6%, 15%, 21% and 24% distributor must meet the required 40 PV purchase each cycle as set up in our DLC Policy to be classified as Active Distributors. DLC encourages distributors to put emphasis on personal retailing and personal use in order to have a healthy DLC business.<br><br></li><li>Bonus checks will be available on the twelfth (12th) day following the cut-off of product sales.<ul><li>The bonus checks, upon instruction, can be:</li><li>remitted to the said Distributor’s bank account through Automatic Bank Transfer. A distributor can utilize their existing Bank of the Philippine Islands (BPI) bank account or open one. DLC will automatically transfer the Semi-Monthly volume bonus to the Distributor’s bank account. Note that the Distributor has to make sure the bank account information is correct. BPI is not the same as BPI Family Bank. For the Volume Bonus Recap, distributors can view and print them from the DLC website.</li><li>claimed from the Head Office or Product Centers. The Company will