onal sales from DLC-branded products.<br></li><li>Any distributor who can break off a 24% line that does at least 4000 PV total sales volume for the cycle and also maintains a non-manager group sales volume of at least 4000 PV for the same cycle of which 40 PV is personal sales from DLC-branded products.<br></li><li>Any distributor who can break off two (2) 24% lines that does at least 4000 PV total sales volume for the cycle and also maintains a non-manager group sales volume of at least 500 PV for the same cycle of which 40 PV is personal sales from DLC-branded products.<br></li><li>Any distributor who can break off three (3) or more 24% lines that does at least 4000 PV total sales volume for the cycle, shall enjoy the benefit of zero (0) PV group requirement for the same cycle with 40 PV as personal sales from DLC-branded products.<br></li><li>can qualify for Semi-Monthly profit sharing.</li></ul><br></li><li>To qualify for Overriding Bonuses from sponsored groups, the 6%, 15%, 21% and 24% distributor must meet the required 40 PV purchase each cycle as set up in our DLC Policy to be classified as Active Distributors. DLC encourages distributors to put emphasis on personal retailing and personal use in order to have a healthy DLC business.<br><br></li><li>Bonus checks will be available on the twelfth (12th) day following the cut-off of product sales.<ul><li>The bonus checks, upon instruction, can be:</li><li>remitted to the said Distributor’s bank account through Automatic Bank Transfer. A distributor can utilize their existing Bank of the Philippine Islands (BPI) bank account or open one. DLC will automatically transfer the Semi-Monthly volume bonus to the Distributor’s bank account. Note that the Distributor has to make sure the bank account information is correct. BPI is not the same as BPI Family Bank. For the Volume Bonus Recap, distributors can view and print them from the DLC website.</li><li>claimed from the Head Office or Product Centers. The Company will issue a Volume Bonus check and the Distributor will have to claim the check from the Head Office or Product Centers.</li></ul><br><br></li><li>0%, 6%, 15%, 21%, 24% distributors will not be able to receive any Override Bonus on any distributor who is at the same level in their sponsored group. However, they will qualify to receive PV from such sources for move-up purposes.<br><br></li><li>There is a no reversion clause at the 6% level but there is a cycle reversion to 6% at the 15%, 21% and 24% levels.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Semi-Monthly Bonus', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '118-revision-v1', '', '', '2021-03-08 23:04:14', '2021-03-08 15:04:14', '', 118, 'https://dlcph.com/read/118-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(325, 2, '2021-03-08 23:04:32', '2021-03-08 15:04:32', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Semi-Monthly Bonus is calculated based on the Pay Out Value (POV) of the products and the percentage is based on the level of the total Group Point Value (GPV) a distributor has accumulated during the cycle. The higher the cycle PV achieved, the higher the percentage will be used to calculate the Semi-Monthly Bonus. This DLC bonus is based not only on the Distributor’s personal purchase but also includes all purchases made by all non-manager distributors under his/her organization. The difference in percentage between his/her Semi-Monthly Bonus and his/her active direct downlines’ Semi-Monthly Bonus will be the Override Bonus.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":120} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://dlcph.com/read/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/chart01.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-120\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The value of 1 PV will be set based on the GDP of each country. For example, in North America 1 PV may be equivalent to US$1 while in Taiwan it may be equivalent to NT$33.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Bonus Structure<br></strong>The bonuses of distributors are structured in the following levels: 0%, 6%, 15%, 21% and 24%.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>The 0% Distributor:</strong><ul><li>- Not qualified to claim any Semi-Monthly Bonus.</li></ul><br></li><li><strong>The 6% Distributor:</strong><ul><li>- is qualified for 6% bonus on all personal sales volume based on POV.</li><li>- is qualified for 6% Override Bonus on all personally sponsored 0% distributors’ group sales volume.</li><li>- is qualified for 0% Override Bonus on all personally sponsored 6% distributors’ group sales volume.</li><li>- must be active by maintaining 40 PV personal sales volume from DLC-branded products for the cycle to receive Semi-Monthly bonus and any over